_pdbx_molecule_features.class     Immunosuppressant 
_pdbx_molecule_features.details   
;CYCLOSPORIN C IS A CYCLIC UNDECAPEPTIDE. CYCLIZATION IS ACHIEVED BY LINKING THE N- AND THE C- TERMINI. CYCLOSPORIN C IS A NATURAL ANALOG OF CYCLOSPORIN A, OBTAINED FROM A DIFFERENT NUTRIENT BROTH AND DIFFERS FROM CYCLOSPORIN A IN RESIDUE 6 (ABA6THR). THIS IS A CYCLOSPORIN C VARIANT THAT DIFFERS AT 1, 3, AND 9 POSITIONS.
;
